'''''Pseudoramibacter''''' is a [[Gram-positive]], strictly [[Anaerobic organism|anaerobic]], non-[[spore]]-forming and non-motile bacterial genus from the family of [[Eubacteriaceae]] with one known species (''[[Pseudoramibacter alactolyticus]]'').<ref>{{cite book|last1=Berman|first1=Jules J.|title=Taxonomic Guide to Infectious Diseases: Understanding the Biologic Classes of Pathogenic Organisms|date=2012|publisher=Academic Press|isbn=9780124159136|language=en}}</ref><ref name=Pseudoramibacter/><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Parker|first1=Charles Thomas|last2=Garrity|first2=George M|title=Nomenclature Abstract for Pseudoramibacter Willems and Collins 1996.|journal=The NamesforLife Abstracts|doi=10.1601/nm.4301|language=en}}</ref><ref name=Bay>{{cite journal|last1=Willems|first1=Anne|last2=Collins|first2=Matthew D.|title=Pseudoramibacter|journal=Bergey's Manual of Systematics of Archaea and Bacteria|date=2015|doi=10.1002/9781118960608.gbm00631|publisher=John Wiley & Sons, Ltd|language=en}}</ref> ''Pseudoramibacter'' bacteria occur in birds.<ref name=Bay/> ''Pseudoramibacter alactolyticus'' is associated with [[endodontic infections]].<ref>{{cite book|last1=Torabinejad|first1=Mahmoud|last2=Fouad|first2=Ashraf|last3=Walton|first3=Richard E.|title=Endodontics - E-Book: Principles and Practice|date=2014|publisher=Elsevier Health Sciences|isbn=9781455754090|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Siqueira JF|first1=Jr|last2=Rôças|first2=IN|title=Pseudoramibacter alactolyticus in primary endodontic infections.|journal=Journal of endodontics|date=November 2003|volume=29|issue=11|pages=735–8|doi=10.1097/00004770-200311000-00012|pmid=14651280}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Carrilho|first1=M. Rocha de Olivera|title=Root Caries: From Prevalence to Therapy|date=2017|publisher=Karger Medical and Scientific Publishers|isbn=9783318061130|language=en}}</ref>

