{{Infobox organization |name = Surface Water Simulation Modelling Programme |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = 1986 |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = |headquarters = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = Bangladesh |members = |language = Bengali |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = http://www.iwmbd.org/ Surface Water Simulation Modelling Programme] |remarks = }}
'''Surface Water Simulation Modelling Programme''' (SWSMP) launched in 1986 by the Ministry of Water Resources of Bangladesh Government under the Master Planning Organization to develop a high level of analytical capabilities by use of state-of-the-art mathematical water modelling which was the genesis of what at present is known as the [[Institute of Water Modelling]] (IWM).<ref name="unbx">{{cite web|title=Institute of Water Modelling|url=http://www.iwmbd.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4&Itemid=5|website=iwmbd.org|accessdate=21 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Surface_Water_Modelling_Centre|title=Surface Water Modelling Centre - Banglapedia|website=en.banglapedia.org|language=en|access-date=2017-12-04}}</ref>
