[[File:Winifred Cullis 1930s.jpg|thumb|300px|Winifred Cullis in the 1930s]]
'''Winifred Cullis''' (2 June 1875 – 13 November 1956) was a physician and academic, and the first woman to hold a professorial chair at a medical school.<ref name="a">{{cite web|url=http://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/a2a/records.aspx?cat=106-7wcu |title=Access to Archives |publisher=The National Archives |date= |accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref>

== Biography ==

Born in [[Gloucester]], Winifred was the youngest daughter of Frederick John and Louisa Cullis. She was educated at [[King Edwards VI High School for Girls, Birmingham]] after which she attended  [[Newnham College, Cambridge]] and then [[London School of Medicine for Women]]. She became professor of physiology at the [[University of London]] in 1919.<ref name="a"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/arts/yourpaintings/paintings/professor-winifred-cullis-18751956-191998 |title=Your Paintings – Professor Winifred Cullis (1875–1956) |publisher=[[BBC]] |date= |accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref>

She was president of the [[British Federation of University Women]] (1925–1929) and the [[International Federation of University Women]] (1929–1932).<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1038/1781266a0| title = Prof. Winifred Cullis, C.B.E| journal = Nature| volume = 178| issue = 4545| pages = 1266| year = 1956}}</ref> She toured the world extensively promoting higher education for women<ref>{{cite web|url=http://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/cgi-bin/paperspast?a=d&cl=search&d=AS19361028.2.171.2.1&srpos=4 |title=Papers Past — Auckland Star — 28 October 1936 — DISTINGUISHED VISITOR. — Professor Winifred Cullis, C.8.E., M.A., D.Sc., UL.D., a past world preside... [truncated&#93; |publisher=Paperspast.natlib.govt.nz |date=28 October 1936 |accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref> and also promoted adult education via radio shows.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/cgi-bin/paperspast?a=d&cl=search&d=AS19320915.2.66&srpos=22 |title=Papers Past — Auckland Star — 15 September 1932 — B.B.C. AS UNIVERSITY |publisher=Paperspast.natlib.govt.nz |date=15 September 1932 |accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref>

The [[International Federation of University Women]] has an award in her honour.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ifuw.org/what-we-do/grants-fellowships/international-awards/ |title=International Awards &#124; International Federation of University Women |publisher=IFUW |date= |accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref>

